In the heart of the image, a Ukrainian baby girl's face materializes with profound serenity, her features etched in soothing shades of cream and baby pink. Her soft skin, illuminated by the lingering light from the solitary candle, appears almost ethereal amidst the stark contrasts of her surroundings. Jagged, charred debris forms the edges of the scene, emphasizing the chaos from which serenity emerges. The candle's golden glow harmonizes with the pastel hues of her skin, casting shadows that dance upon her closed eyes--a symbol of peaceful slumber even as she floats above the ruins. Delicate angel wings extend behind her back, barely visible; their existence seems woven from light and shadow, evoking a dreamlike atmosphere. The inscriptions 'R.I.P.', '08.07.24', 'KYIV', and 'OHMATDIT' are tastefully integrated, commemorating history and lending profundity to the artistry. In the distant background, hints of green and blue surface, echoing the night sky, while the darkness elsewhere adds to the somber ambience. This celestial child, encircled by the glow of the defiant candle, becomes the visual and emotional center, a luminous beacon of innocence and hope amidst a storm of ashes and memories.